commits.commitMessage:
Refactor the import namespaces to align with LeTP.

LeTP recently refactored to include namespace for libraries.
e.g. "import swilog" will be "from pytest_letp.lib import swilog"
This way, we can easily see what module is instead of using
the global namespace.

To refactor the import in different files. The goal is
to have pytest test discovery work for the tests.

Misc:
Remove some unused imports.

Resolves: LETEST-6004
Change-Id: Ic102de24d47296629b34764385ff5a3868c36bef
commits.subject: Refactor the import namespaces to align with LeTP.
